{
  "stem": "9908.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Ozorkow-- there were-- 90% of the Jews were very religious.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Like I told you, they wore kippahs.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They wore their little hats.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They will go into shul three times a day-- two times a day-- in the morning, for the morning prayers.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Then the Mincha Maariv was a big thing.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Even Hanukkah, when we had-- every Jewish holiday was a-- a big event.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "That's was the Polish-Jewish life.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Like I say, if somebody wasn't from-- and he wanted to buy meat from a-- not a kosher butcher-- he hid himself to go in to see that nobody sees him that he's buying non-kosher food.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was very religious.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "One incident I can tell you.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "On Pesach, all the Jewish bakeries were closed.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "The last day after Pesach, one Yid-- he wasn't very firm.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "He lit already the oven to bake for the next day for bread, because people after Pesach were running out of bread.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "As the-- the people-- the firm people saw the smoke coming from the chimney, they went into the Rabbi, and the Rabbi went there.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And he made a big, big thing about it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "This was a Jewish-- that's why you know, the Jews-- the Jews lived a very, very orthodox life.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "My father was a kohen.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "He was going to all [NON-ENGLISH] in the city.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "A lot of times I went along with him.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "It was very nice to see it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And life was in general very beautiful in the primitive country.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Then it didn't-- like-- like I say, every Jew was a Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "If you watch the film, you can describe exactly the Polish Yidden in Poland-- with the tzitzits, with the little hats.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Nobody there would-- would do something wrong about religion.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Shabbos Friday night-- [NON-ENGLISH] closed all the shops.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
